01:36:37.640 --> 01:36:40.680
&gt;&gt; My question is for
Professor Parpola and others.

01:36:40.680 --> 01:36:46.460 position:56%
We've heard a lot about the
Assyrians as dynasts and as monarchs

01:36:46.460 --> 01:36:50.450
and so forth, but who did they
rule in Northern Mesopotamia?

01:36:50.450 --> 01:36:52.380
Who were the Assyrian people?

01:36:52.380 --> 01:36:53.680
Were they nomads?

01:36:53.680 --> 01:36:55.450
Were they pastoralists?

01:36:55.450 --> 01:36:58.120
Were they tribally organized?

01:36:58.120 --> 01:37:01.600
Who were these people
in Northern Mesopotamia

01:37:01.600 --> 01:37:07.160
or Anatole or to the Mediterranean?

01:37:07.160 --> 01:37:15.550 position:56%
&gt;&gt; Simo Parpola: Well, the Assyrians
are one of the indigenous people

01:37:15.550 --> 01:37:21.020
of Mesopotamia who
are already attested

01:37:21.020 --> 01:37:23.890
in various sources,
Sumerian sources.

01:37:23.890 --> 01:37:31.030
So, the city of [inaudible] is
the old center of Assyrians,

01:37:31.030 --> 01:37:38.660
which was an important commercial
place in the third millennium B.C.

01:37:38.660 --> 01:37:46.540
And it became part of
the Old Akkadian Empire,

01:37:46.540 --> 01:37:53.280
and there was a governor of the
Akkadian Empire in that city.

01:37:53.280 --> 01:37:59.300
Later on after the collapse of
the Old Akkadian Empire the city

01:37:59.300 --> 01:38:04.850
of [inaudible] continued
its long-distance trade

01:38:04.850 --> 01:38:07.160
with Anatolia, for instance.

01:38:07.160 --> 01:38:19.890
And in the early 2000, about
1950 B.C., we see the rise

01:38:19.890 --> 01:38:25.790
of the first Assyrian kingdom

01:38:25.790 --> 01:38:30.390
that soon controlled large
parts of Northern Mesopotamia.

01:38:30.390 --> 01:38:33.230
So, they were not nomads
in the sense,

01:38:33.230 --> 01:38:36.050
but they were originally traders.

01:38:36.050 --> 01:38:41.820
And they carried out such a
lucrative trade with Anatolia

01:38:41.820 --> 01:38:46.380
because they monopolized, for
instance, the trade in tin,

01:38:46.380 --> 01:38:49.960
which was essential
for producing thrones.

01:38:49.960 --> 01:38:54.330
So, they became very
wealthy and very ambitious,

01:38:54.330 --> 01:39:00.640
and became empire builders.

01:39:00.640 --> 01:39:12.370
And the Old Assyrian Empire
collapsed quite roughly soon,

01:39:12.370 --> 01:39:22.430 position:56%
but in the so-called [inaudible] age
1300 before Christ we see the rise

01:39:22.430 --> 01:39:26.370
of the Middle Assyrian Empire,
which is really the same thing

01:39:26.370 --> 01:39:30.010
as the New Assyrian
Empire from which I talked.

01:39:30.010 --> 01:39:35.310
It dominated for 700 years
with little ups and downs,

01:39:35.310 --> 01:39:38.740
the political scene
in the Near East.

01:39:38.740 --> 01:39:45.150
Well, as I tried to explain
not very successfully,

01:39:45.150 --> 01:39:52.710
the citizens of the [inaudible]
Empire really collectively shared

01:39:52.710 --> 01:39:56.390
the Assyrian national
identity in addition

01:39:56.390 --> 01:40:02.060
to what ethnic memories they
may have had of their origins.

01:40:02.060 --> 01:40:08.130
But when Assyria collapsed this
national identity was changed

01:40:08.130 --> 01:40:15.040
into ethnic identity, because there
was no Assyrian Empire any longer.

01:40:15.040 --> 01:40:23.140
But the Assyrians insisted they
knew what they were, and the things

01:40:23.140 --> 01:40:26.390
that really connected them
was the language, and,

01:40:26.390 --> 01:40:28.380
of course, also their religion.

01:40:28.380 --> 01:40:32.380
I would have explained if I had
time that there are many elements

01:40:32.380 --> 01:40:36.290
in Christianity for instance
the [inaudible] doctrine

01:40:36.290 --> 01:40:38.700
that goes back to Assyria.

01:40:38.700 --> 01:40:47.080
Also the idea of Christ
as the savior of mankind.

01:40:47.080 --> 01:40:52.960
This is the role that the Assyrian
kings performed in the world.

01:40:52.960 --> 01:40:57.670
They were the incarnations
of [inaudible] say the son

01:40:57.670 --> 01:41:00.160
of the Supreme [inaudible].

01:41:00.160 --> 01:41:06.540
And also I would have talked
about the third element

01:41:06.540 --> 01:41:10.410
in Assyria religion, namely,
the belief in the Holy Ghost.

01:41:10.410 --> 01:41:14.770
But there was no time for it.

01:41:16.580 --> 01:41:21.330
Anyhow, so, when we talked about
Assyrians we have to distinguish

01:41:21.330 --> 01:41:26.130
between two things-- the
Assyrians of the time of the empire

01:41:26.130 --> 01:41:31.540
and then the Assyrians
that are the same people,

01:41:31.540 --> 01:41:36.100
but have a slightly different
identity to say despite the fact

01:41:36.100 --> 01:41:45.210
that Aramaic was also spoken
in Assyrian Empire, of course,

01:41:45.210 --> 01:41:50.480
the people usually identify
the old Syrians with Akkadians.

01:41:50.480 --> 01:41:53.120
But they were the same
as [inaudible],

01:41:53.120 --> 01:41:59.710
but they were Aramaic
[inaudible] mainly,

01:41:59.710 --> 01:42:02.480
and believed in more or
less the same things.

01:42:02.480 --> 01:42:03.880
&gt;&gt; Mary Jane Deeb:
Thank you very much.

01:42:03.880 --> 01:42:05.190
One more question.

01:42:05.190 --> 01:42:07.780
We have someone here, and
then we'll take a break.

01:42:07.780 --> 01:42:09.080
&gt;&gt; Thank you.

01:42:09.080 --> 01:42:13.540
My question is I understand they
were indigenous people, Assyrian,

01:42:13.540 --> 01:42:20.150
so they were not migrated from
any other places prehistorically

01:42:20.150 --> 01:42:22.640
like the Medes or [inaudible]
which they came

01:42:22.640 --> 01:42:26.140
from I think today's [inaudible]?

01:42:26.140 --> 01:42:27.440
&gt;&gt; Simo Parpola: No.

01:42:27.440 --> 01:42:29.660 position:56%
They were indigenous to Mesopotamia.

01:42:29.660 --> 01:42:33.930
For instance, the Arameans
which later gave their language

01:42:33.930 --> 01:42:42.940
to the whole empire were
originally inhabitants

01:42:42.940 --> 01:42:45.720
of [inaudible], [inaudible]
in Syria.

01:42:45.720 --> 01:42:52.410
And then at the end of the
seventh millennium B.C.

01:42:52.410 --> 01:42:59.200
when climatic conditions started
to [inaudible] there was a period

01:42:59.200 --> 01:43:03.580
of warming which meant fewer rains.

01:43:03.580 --> 01:43:07.750
These Arameans, who were
nomads and had multiplied

01:43:07.750 --> 01:43:13.820
under more favorable climatic
conditions, started to move

01:43:13.820 --> 01:43:18.270
from [inaudible] to other
parts of the Near East,

01:43:18.270 --> 01:43:21.870
spreading all over
the Assyrian Empire.

01:43:21.870 --> 01:43:25.740
That was the beginning
of the spread of Aramaic.

01:43:25.740 --> 01:43:31.970
But they are still part of the
historical ancient Near East.

